    "created_at": "2016-03-29T21:44:24Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-29T21:48:52Z",
    "body": "Oh, yeah I use Web workers for some game logic too. But, the main issue is the arcade physics is tied to RAF. So if a player joins a game and starts shooting fireballs to attack a mob and then if another player joins and that player is alt-tabbed (window is not active), he won't receive notification of those fireballs being sent on his screen. (The server will send them and Chrome/Electron will get them from the websocket, but his client won't  update the location of those fireballs until he activates his screen again). \n\nI mean, you could maybe tie the physics engine through Web Workers... but I'm not sure if that is a good idea. I could be wrong though lol\n"
